5:
What do mean, you can't find
Ayumu?
9:
He likely made contact with the
Abyss.
13:
The Abyss? What are you talking
about?
17:
I suppose you could describe it as...
a tunnel to a far-off world.
19:
Alk was right there the moment two
worlds merged. Something like this
was bound to happen.
27:
Ah, that being said, you needn't
worry.
36:
I agree. Alk will surely return to us. Do
not worry, Nao.
40:
It was Alk and Stella's desire that
brought your home to Palpebra. I'm
sure that same desire will guide Alk
back as well.
43:
Or... could it be that you do not
believe in your friend?
50:
Dammiiit! How can he get our hopes
up like that? And with such a flimsy
reason too...
54:
Actually, I think I get it. I believe in
Yumu.
58:
I mean, he came back to us once
already, didn't he? I'm sure he can
do it again!
62:
I-I mean, it's not that I DON'T believe
in him... It's just...
66:
Wait, forget about that! What's with
that pretty boy?! How can he say
such dark crap with a smile on his
fac—
74:
Pretty boy? Am I to assume that
means you find me pretty? Thank
you!
82:
So what... You looking for me or
something?
86:
That I was. I have a question for you,
Shota Inori...
90:
What is your relationship with Alk?
Surely you don't mean to betray him
again, do you?
93:
Alk and I are partners in crime. If you
are Alk's enemy, that makes you my
enemy as well.
105:
Sho's a friend of Yumu's! And mine
too, although he mostly just listens
to me ramble.
113:
...You're better off asking Ayumu. All I
wanna do is pay him back.
117: Is that so? Then this is perfect!
120:
I know I said Alk would make his way
back to us, but I don't intend to just
stand around waiting.
123:
Shota Inori... You and I are going to
look for him.
129:
Hey, uh... Why me? Ayumu's got tons
of friends. Like that tiger guy.
133:
Well, the residents of Starview
Village share a deep connection
with "Alk." As such, it was best for
them to stay behind to serve as an
anchor.
135:
On the other hand, you share a
strong connection with "Ayumu
Nagihara," correct?
139:
I mean... I feel like Yuki or Nao
would've been a better choi—
151: You know what? You go on ahead.
154: I'll just stay back here and wait.
158:
You do realize if we separate, we'll
have to go looking for YOU next,
correct?
162:
I won't be that far off. As long as
you're in my sight, it should be fine,
right?
166:
But... Are you sure? I thought you
wanted to pay Alk back.
170:
Look, I just don't know how to face
him, okay?
179:
Arrrgh! How the hell did I end up
being such a loser?! I'm so LAME!
195:
You've made quite the mess,
partner.
203:
By the way, you should prepare
yourself for an interesting welcome
back. Everyone's been very worried,
you see.
225: This is bad! Like, BAD bad!
228:
Oh, looks like you're ready to face Alk
after all! Anything you want to say to
him, Shota?
232: Oh for—NOT NOW! We need to—
238:
Dammit! It's here! Why didn't you tell
me there were giant monsters
here?! Do something, Ayumu!
241: An Antibody? No... What is that thing?
247:
Why are you laughing?! We're
gonna die!
251:
I was just thinking... Leave it to Shota
to ruin our heartfelt reunion.
259: Anyway, let's get out of here, Sho!
268:
You think we can take THAT by
ourselves?! But try to hold him off,
will ya?
272:
Oh, I can't fight by the way, so it's all
up to you.
283:
We're dead! So dead! Dead, dead,
DEAD!
287:
AND WHY AM I THE ONLY ONE
FIGHTING?!
291: Ahaha, this is fun, isn't it?
